me characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Normand, Adrien, Lucien, Marcel, Aime, Andre, Camille, Fernand, Pierre, Raoul, Aldege.","French: habitational name from (La) Gamache or Gamaches, the name of several places in various parts of France, e.g. in Somme, possibly named from the Celtic elements <i>cam</i> ‘bent, winding’ + <i>apia</i> ‘water’.","History: Nicolas Gamache from Saint-Illiers-la-Ville in Yvelines, France, married Élisabeth-Ursule Cloutier in Château-Richer, QC, in 1676."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Godfrey","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old French name <i>Godefroy</i>, which is of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>god</i> ‘god’ (or <i>gōd</i> ‘good’) + <i>fred</i>, <i>frid</i> ‘peace’. This was adopted by the Normans, and brought to England by immigrants from the Low Countries and France. It was borne by a Norman saint (  <i>c.</i>1066–1115 ) who became bishop of Amiens. There has been considerable confusion with   Geoffrey ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Godfrey I de Gamaches was born about 1130, in Gamaches-en-Vexin, Eure, Normandy, France as the son of Thomas De Gamage I and Unknown. He married Alice Carpet. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1176, in Shropshire, England, at the age of 47."},"et":{"about 1130–1176":"umbes 1130–1176","1130–1176":"1130–1176","1134–Female":"1134–Surnud","1150–1240":"1150–1240","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1100–1129":"1100–1129","–Female":"Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1129":"1129","after 1129":"pärast 1129","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","1176":"1176","1240":"1240","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","about 1130":"umbes 1130","Manor of Stottesden, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Gamaches-en-Vexin, Eure, Duché de Normandie":"Gamaches-en-Vexin, Eure, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Gamaches-en-Vexin, Eure, Duché de  Normandie":"Gamaches-en-Vexin, Eure, No